The article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris at the ninth Summit of the Americas in Los Angeles, California. She begins by expressing her excitement at being back in her home state and welcoming everyone to the summit. Harris emphasizes the importance of California as a place where dreams become reality and discusses the ambitions and progress made in the Western Hemisphere over the past 28 years. She highlights the impact of the region on the security and prosperity of the United States and calls for partnerships and collaborations to address challenges such as the climate crisis, food insecurity, economic inequality, corruption, and gender-based violence. Harris sees the summit as an opportunity to launch new initiatives, have meaningful conversations, and build new partnerships. She concludes by urging everyone to commit to building a more prosperous and inclusive future for the Western Hemisphere.